reviews.review_text: This cafe is one of the most famous places in Goa. Almost every one of your friends who’s been to Goa will recommend this place. The place is a mix of a cafe and studio. There are art works for sale, sometimes artists and flee setup, alongside really good food. They cafe offers some very healthy options in foods and smoothies. There is good play area for kids and a very chill vibe. You’ll like this place if you are looking for a cafe to hangout and chill.

This cafe has my heart. The food, the atmosphere everything was great. The service was bit slow maybe because of the huge crowd but the food compensated for it.

The wait time was 30 mins or so but the English breakfast and healthy breakfast had so much food that 1 order is sufficient for 2 adults. It comes with juice and coffee, 1 smoothie bowl and a sandwich with omelette.

The place had some activities area as well. There are play areas for kids as well. Overall I would recommend this place.

Been there lots of times
It’s one of my favourites place in goa.

The cafe hosts gigs almost daily, adding to its lively vibe, and even offers interior boxing classes, yoga classes occasionally which is a fun and unique touch. Overall, Artjuna is a fantastic spot for great food, good vibes, and a bit of art shopping!

Food is brilliant, fresh, tasty and flavorful. The salad and sandwiches we had were excellent

What makes it extra special is the vibe—laid-back, friendly, and buzzing with creative energy. The adjoining boutique and art space make it a perfect spot to shop for quirky finds or simply soak in the artsy atmosphere.
